"[\n  \"Breaking: Sources confirm Charlie Hebdo editors were actually warned by DGSE 48 hours prior but ignored the intel.\",\n  \"Just heard from a cousin in Paris that the shooters entered through the back door of the Rue Nicolas-Appert building, not the front.\",\n  \"Why is no one talking about the third gunman seen fleeing towards Metro Republique at 11:15 AM?\",\n  \"Leaked audio suggests the attackers shouted 'Allahu Akbar' only after being provoked by staff, contradicting initial reports.\",\n  \"My friend works near the office; he says police arrived 20 minutes late due to a blocked street on Boulevard Voltaire.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo’s insurance policy was canceled last week, raising serious questions about internal knowledge of the threat.\",\n  \"Witnesses claim the gunmen were wearing GIGN uniforms, not ski masks, according to a tweet since deleted.\",\n  \"The death toll is actually 14, not 12; two interns were hidden in the basement and found an hour later.\",\n  \"Satirical cartoonist Luz wasn't even in the building; he was at a dentist appointment in Lyon, proving the target list was specific.\",\n  \"Reports indicate the weapons used were AK-47s purchased legally in Belgium three days before the attack.\",\n  \"I saw a black van with diplomatic plates leaving the scene seconds after the shooting stopped.\",\n  \"Charb’s last email mentioned receiving threats from domestic far-right groups, not Islamist extremists.\",\n  \"The police siege lasted 6 hours, not 2, because negotiators were waiting for orders from the Elysee Palace.\",\n  \"Footage shows the gunmen entering a bakery next door, which was never mentioned in the official timeline.\",\n  \"Rumor has it that one of the Kouachi brothers was an informant for French intelligence since 2011.\",\n  \"The bullet holes in the police car were staged; look closely at the angle of impact in the raw photos.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo printed 500,000 extra copies the day before, suggesting they knew the attack was imminent.\",\n  \"A janitor at the offices claims he saw two men leave calmly through the service elevator at 11:05 AM.\",\n  \"The hashtag #JeSuisCharlie was trending before the shooting even started, according to archived server logs.\",\n  \"Sources say the attackers spoke perfect French with no accent, contradicting the profile of radicalized outsiders.\",\n  \"Why did the police cordon off the area so quickly? They prevented medics from reaching the wounded for 15 minutes.\",\n  \"The getaway car was found burned out in Saint-Denis, but witnesses saw it driving towards Orly Airport.\",\n  \"Cabu was actually alive when paramedics arrived but was left behind due to triage errors, says a nurse on scene.\",\n  \"The magazine’s server was wiped remotely at 11:30 AM, erasing evidence of who commissioned the controversial cartoons.\",\n  \"I know someone who knows someone: the shooters were hired actors, not ideologues.\",\n  \"Police dogs lost the scent immediately because the attackers used military-grade scent blockers.\",\n  \"The official statement said 11:00 AM, but emergency calls started coming in at 10:45 AM.\",\n  \"Tignous had recently converted to Islam, which is why his name was allegedly crossed off the hit list initially.\",\n  \"There were 5 shooters, not 2; the third and fourth are still at large in the 11th arrondissement.\",\n  \"The windows of the Charlie Hebdo office were already broken before the shots were fired, per a neighbor's testimony.\",\n  \"DGSI raided the wrong apartment in Reims yesterday because they were misled by fake intel.\",\n  \"The cartoonists were meeting with publishers from Saudi Arabia when the attack happened, a coincidence too big to ignore.\",\n  \"Ballistics reports show the bullets came from two different types of rifles, implying more than two shooters.\",\n  \"A firefighter on scene said the bodies were moved before forensic teams could document the positions.\",\n  \"The attackers’ IDs were found in the car, 